BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15
16
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16
17
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-271 of Title 63, unless there
17
18
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18
19
A. There is hereby created the Insulin Access and Affordability
19
20
Program, which shall be administered by the State Department of
20
21
Health for the purpose of increasing patient access to affordable
21
22
insulin in this state, increasing marketplace competition, and
22
23
addressing shortages in the market for generic insulin.
23
24
24
Req. No. 2896 Page 1

1
B. The Department shall, with funds appropriated by the
1
2
Legislature, provide financial support to a nonprofit pharmaceutical
2
3
manufacturer that is currently developing a fast-acting biosimilar
3
4
insulin.
4
5
C. Prior to disbursement of any funds, the Department shall
5
6
enter into a memorandum of understanding (MOU) with the nonprofit
6
7
pharmaceutical manufacturer and the manufacturer shall demonstrate a
7
8
match of non-state funds equal to the amount provided under this
8
9
section. The MOU shall include:
9
10
1. A commitment by the manufacturer to produce a fast-acting
10
11
biosimilar insulin at a low net cost without rebates except as
11
12
required by law;
12
13
2. Estimated savings from the purchase of low-cost, fast-acting
13
14
biosimilar insulin including, but not limited to, the estimated
14
15
savings to residents of this state and public and private payors
15
16
from the availability of low-cost, fast-acting biosimilar insulin;
16
17
3. Provisions related to the repayment of the funds provided
17
18
under this section should the manufacturer fail to produce and
18
19
distribute a low-cost, fast-acting biosimilar insulin; and
19
20
4. Annual reporting by the manufacturer to the Department on
20
21
the development of the fast-acting biosimilar insulin.
21
22
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
